text: Ushkonyr (, Üşqonyr), formerly known as Shamalgan (, Şamalğan) or Chemolgan, () is a rural community near Almaty in Kazakhstan. It is notable as the birthplace of former Kazakh president Nursultan Nazarbayev.The President of Kazakhstan Nursultan Nazarbayev Embassy of Kazakhstan in Israel ==References== Category:Populated places in Almaty Region
title: Ushkonyr
